@startuml
' @id(SEQ-ARCH-DIFF)
' @ref(USE-TRACK-ARCH)
' @desc(SEQ-ARCH-DIFF, "How `mdd arch diff` and `mdd arch status` run. diff: parse the working .mdd/architecture/*.yml, read the base version at a git ref (default HEAD) via git show, compute a structured ArchDiff, print it (text or --json). status: parse the working spec, summarize counts + decision statuses, run check() against the model-registry ids, print, and exit non-zero on any ArchViolation. The same check() is folded into `mdd validate` as WARNING-level OCL-ARCH-* rules (inert when there is no spec).")
title mdd arch diff and status (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Agent
participant "mdd arch" as CLI
participant "ArchitectureSpec::load" as Load
participant "git show ref" as Git
participant "diff() / check()" as Core

alt mdd arch diff
  Agent -> CLI : mdd arch diff [--base ref]
  CLI -> Load : parse working .mdd/architecture
  CLI -> Git : read .mdd/architecture at base ref
  Git --> CLI : base spec (empty if absent)
  CLI -> Core : diff(base, head)
  Core --> CLI : ArchDiff (added / removed / changed)
else mdd arch status
  Agent -> CLI : mdd arch status
  CLI -> Load : parse working .mdd/architecture
  CLI -> Core : check(spec, model ids)
  Core --> CLI : violations (non-zero exit if any)
end
CLI --> Agent : report (text or --json)
@enduml
